data.title: Where Kentucky and its opponents stand in CBS preseason rankings
data.meta_description: Kentucky is eyeing a ninth straight bowl appearance in 2024.
data.text:
Preseason rankings are rolling in with the start of college football season rapidly approaching. The first college football game, at the FBS level, is August 24th when Florida State takes on Georgia Tech in Atlanta.

Kentucky will open its 2024 season the following Saturday against Southern Mississippi in Lexington. It will be their first season in the new SEC with Texas and Oklahoma joining the conference this season.

CBS Sports recently revealed its preseason rankings of all 134 FBS teams, with Kentucky checking in at No. 32.

According to CBS, Kentucky is the 10th highest-ranked team in the SEC, which illustrates how good and deep the SEC will be this season.

Georgia checks in at No. 1, followed by No. 4 Texas, No. 5 Alabama, No. 6 Ole Miss, No. 11 Missouri, No. 12 LSU, No. 15 Tennessee, No. 18 Oklahoma and No. 20 Texas A&M.

Kentucky faces Georgia, Ole Miss, Tennessee, and Texas this season.

The Louisville Cardinals, who Kentucky hosts in the regular-season finale, check in at No. 26.

Southern Miss, who Kentucky opens the season with, checks in at No. 116.

Ohio, who comes to Kentucky in Week 4, is ranked No. 90.

The Wildcats are projected to finish 11th in the SEC this season, ahead of Florida, South Carolina, Arkansas, Mississippi State, and Vanderbilt.

Where do you think the Cats should be ranked? Let us know in the comments section!
